.TH "sg_nents_for_len" 9 "sg_nents_for_len" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sg_nents_for_len \- return total count of entries in scatterlist needed to satisfy the supplied length
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sg_nents_for_len
.BI "(struct scatterlist *sg "  ","
.BI "u64 len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sg" 12
The scatterlist
.IP "len" 12
The total required length
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Determines the number of entries in sg that are required to meet
the supplied length, taking into acount chaining as well
.SH "RETURN"
the number of sg entries needed, negative error on failure
